{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_10","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' results/_codex/exec-infrastructure_gate-001/prompt.md\"","aggregated_output":"Read `AGENTS.md`, `START_HERE_FOR_CODEX.md`, and the benchmark/Fermi document. Complete only the infrastructure gate. Do not launch a final scientific run.\n\nInspect the environment, initialize/commit the repository if needed, run the 3M model check, training benchmarks at sequence lengths 64 and 128, and the short devinterp sampler smoke test. Save all logs and JSONs under `results/00_infrastructure_gate/`. Diagnose failures rather than hiding them. Update the state files and recalculate project runtime/cost. Keep each launched command within the time budget the orchestrator granted for this tick.\n\nReturn a structured gate decision. Under unattended orchestration, the operator's pre-authorization (see \"Unattended autonomous operation\" in `AGENTS.md`) stands in for per-run human approval, bounded by the hard budget cap and the wall-clock deadline.\n\n\n---\n## Orchestrator directive for this tick\n- Time budget: 0.500 wall-clock hours (launch bounded jobs with --max-hours within this; poll and kill as you judge best).\n- Task: Rerun the CUDA/infrastructure gate after the operator-side driver repair, but first perform a quick non-mutating check of `nvidia-smi`, PyTorch CUDA visibility, GPU name, driver/runtime versions, and free VRAM. If CUDA is still unavailable or `nvidia-smi` cannot communicate with the driver, update `state/current_status.json`, `state/decision_log.md`, and `state/experiment_registry.csv` with a fresh blocked infrastructure diagnostic and stop without attempting pilot work. Success criterion: `nvidia-smi` works, PyTorch reports one CUDA device with expected L4-class VRAM and at least 25% headroom, and the complete TinyStories-3M train-save-reload-evaluate-sample loop is either passed or produces a concrete infrastructure-gate artifact under `results/00_infrastructure_gate/<run_id>/`.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
